👉 String in Java 

A String is a sequence of characters. In Java, strings are objects of the String class.
Strings are immutable and cannot be changed in JAVA.

A string is instantiated as follows : 

String name;
name = new String("Prince")

String is a class but can be used like a datatype : 

    String name = "Prince";

Here name is reference and Prince is Object

👉 Different ways to print in JAVA : We can use the following ways to print in JAVA : 

1. System.out.print() --> No newline at the end
2. System.out.println() -> Prints a new line at the end
3. System.out.printf()
4. System.out.format()

System.out.printf("%c" , ch)

%c is for character 
%d is for int
%s is for string

For example : 

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String name = new String("Prince");
        System.out.println(name);
    }
}

👉 String Methods : String Methods operate on JAVA strings. They can be used to find length of the String, convert to lowercase etc.

